node.text:
⠀

1️⃣ Location, location, location
2️⃣ Make your money on the buy
3️⃣ Timing is key
⠀
Let’s unpack these…
⠀
With location, one of the most important metrics I look for are areas with high density. More people leads to more demand and vise versa. In commercial, it’s also much harder to attract great tenants & find good vendors to work with in lower density areas.
⠀
Making money on the buy means buying a property at a discounted price. In today’s market I look to buy properties for at least a 30% discount from replacement cost which you can learn by studying a market the comparable properties in an area.
⠀
Real estate is cyclical which is why timing is key. Every state, city, and even submarkets within a city have their own cycles so make sure to keep this in mind when pulling the trigger on investment properties.
⠀
And after following these principles, what is the top way to stand apart as a successful investor? Creative ways of adding value to your properties. This is why I love commercial real estate bc it gives you the most opportunities for adding value and therefore create the largest returns.
⠀
With that said, you should never sit on your hands as there are always great deals to be found in any market which I teach you how in my free training video linked in my bio 👊🏼

node.text:
One of my favorite wealth hacks in real estate:
⠀
Within a year before selling a property I always do a cash-out refinance when available to pull out my equity because it’s tax-free and gives me more working capital to deploy.
⠀
Then I go ahead and do a 1031 exchange when selling the property which is a regulation in the US allowing you to roll over your capital gains to another property tax-free.
⠀
And it’s important you don’t refinance with a loan that has a hefty pre-payment penalty because you will be paying the bank soon after selling the property. So I usually go with lenders like regional banks and credit unions who typically don’t have a pre-payment penalty clause.
⠀
Want to get coached by me and learn all of my investing strategies? Check out the training video linked in my bio 👊🏼😊

node.text:
First steps to get started in real estate if you’re young with little to no money & no steady job yet:
⠀
1. Become a licensed agent
⠀
2. Find a great brokerage to work at in the asset class you want to be in
⠀
3. Build your network & learn the market to start finding great opportunities
⠀
4. Wholesale or represent deals to the investor network you build
⠀
5. Eventually you will have enough capital to invest in your own deals 👊
⠀
If this is you and you’re looking to get started in real estate then my Real Estate Starter program will show you exactly how.
⠀
Check it out by clicking the link in my bio 🏢📈

node.text:
I love office buildings right now bc they are not in demand and there is 4 million sqft vacancy is just Orange County alone compared to 1.3 million sqft vacancy in 2008.
⠀
This creates opportunity for buying at a discount, and the biggest opportunity I see currently is repurposing the office space - especially to medical.
⠀
Medical office is still in high demand and the #1 criteria for repurposing is keeping a 6:1 parking ratio.
⠀
This has always been my investing strategy: buy low, add value, and sell high. While that never changes, the method in which you do it does, such as repurposing assets to what’s in demand today.
⠀
If you want to learn my investing blueprint on how I scaled from a $1M to $100M portfolio in only 6 years & where I'm finding great deals today, check out the new training video I released linked in my bio 🏠👉🏼🏢

node.text:
talking farsi to my fellow Iranians about this special Bugatti once belonged to Shah of Iran 😊

Today I’m delighted to have this very special bugatti here in my gallery! This is really one of a kind that belong to shah of Iran! Enjoy the video and Thank you for all your kind comments.
-
‎امروز من از داشتن این بوگاتی بسیار خاص اینجا در گالری خود خوشحالم! این واقعاً یکی از مواردی است که متعلق به شاه ایران است! از ویدیو لذت ببرید و از همه نظرات لطف شما سپاسگزارم 
.
#parchambalast #shahsbugatti #1of1

node.text:
I'm a cyclical, contrarian investor. When everyone is buying, I'm slowing down. When people are running away from an asset class, I'm running towards it bc I see tremendous opportunity in buying distressed assets that I can add value to.
⠀
With that said, there are always great deals to be found in any market, and I'm especially seeing great opportunities in the office market right now.

Currently have a couple of deals in the pipeline each of which I expect will net me multiple 7-figures.

And this process works on all deal sizes - big and small. If you want to learn my investment strategy, check out "How To Invest In Commercial Real Estate" in my bio link🎯

node.text:
⠀

1️⃣ Location, location, location
2️⃣ Make your money on the buy
3️⃣ Timing is key
⠀
Let’s unpack these…
⠀
With location, one of the most important metrics I look for are areas with high density. More people leads to more demand and vise versa. In commercial, it’s also much harder to attract great tenants & find good vendors to work with in lower density areas.
⠀
Making money on the buy means buying a property at a discounted price. In today’s market I look to buy properties for at least a 30% discount from replacement cost which you can learn by studying a market the comparable properties in an area.
⠀
Real estate is cyclical which is why timing is key. Every state, city, and even submarkets within a city have their own cycles so make sure to keep this in mind when pulling the trigger on investment properties.
⠀
And after following these principles, what is the top way to stand apart as a successful investor? Creative ways of adding value to your properties. This is why I love commercial real estate bc it gives you the most opportunities for adding value and therefore create the largest returns.
⠀
With that said, you should never sit on your hands as there are always great deals to be found in any market which I teach you how in my free training video linked in my bio 👊🏼

node.text:
Discipline is doing something when you don't feel like doing it.
⠀
When you don't feel like doing something and that voice in your head starts giving you excuses on why you can push it off, that's when you MUST do it bc it proves to yourself that you're COMMITTED to your goals and vision more than how you feel in that moment, which creates a new level of internal growth. Do this enough times and it starts to become easy until eventually, it's second nature 👊🏼
